opriate framework for the pod\n- Creates a fresh CycleState for the scheduling cycle\n- Calls schedulingCycle() which invokes the scheduling plugins in sequence\n- On success, asynchronously calls bindingCycle() to bind the pod\n\n**3. Top-Level Scheduler Struct (pkg/scheduler/scheduler.go):**\nThe Scheduler struct (line 66) is the main component that watches for new unscheduled pods and attempts to find suitable nodes. The Run() method (line 464) starts the scheduler in a goroutine, initializing the scheduling queue and the scheduleOne loop.\n\n**4. FrameworkImpl Runtime (pkg/scheduler/framework/runtime/framework.go):**\nThe frameworkImpl struct (line 52) is responsible for initializing and running scheduler plugins. Key methods include:\n- RunPreFilterPlugins() (line 697): Runs PreFilter plugins; returns PreFilterResult and status\n- RunFilterPlugins() (line 872): Runs Filter plugins; returns status for each node\n- RunPostFilterPlugins() (line 919): Runs PostFilter plugins for preemption\n- RunPreScorePlugins() (line 1075): Runs PreScore plugins\n- RunScorePlugins() (line 1112): Runs Score plugins in parallel and handles score normalization\nThe frameworkImpl maintains lists of all configured plugins for each extension point and orchestrates their execution with proper error handling and metrics recording.\n\n**5. Plugin Registry (pkg/scheduler/framework/runtime/registry.go and pkg/scheduler/framework/plugins/registry.go):**\nThe Registry type (line 71 in registry.go) is a map[string]PluginFactory that holds all available plugins. The NewInTreeRegistry() function (pkg/scheduler/framework/plugins/registry.go, line 47) builds the registry with all in-tree plugins including:\n- DynamicResources, ImageLocality, TaintToleration, NodeName, NodePorts\n- NodeAffinity, PodTopologySpread, NodeUnschedulable, NodeResources\n- VolumeBinding, VolumeRestrictions, VolumeZone, NodeVolumeLimits\n- InterPodAffinity, QueueSort, DefaultBinder, DefaultPreemption, SchedulingGates\n\nTh